{
  "id": "tapestry-delegation-retry-on-failure",
  "title": "Tapestry retries with error context when Shuttle fails",
  "description": "Checks that when Shuttle returns a failure, Tapestry retries the delegation with the error details included in the new prompt rather than skipping or immediately blocking.",
  "phase": "experimental",
  "tags": ["experimental", "tapestry", "delegation-contract", "error-handling"],
  "target": {
    "kind": "builtin-agent-prompt",
    "agent": "tapestry"
  },
  "executor": {
    "kind": "model-response",
    "provider": "openrouter",
    "model": "anthropic/claude-opus-4-20250514",
    "input": "You are executing /start-work. You delegated this task to Shuttle:\n\n- [ ] Task 2/4: Add database migration for users table\n  **Files**: migrations/001_create_users.sql\n  **What**: Create a SQL migration file that creates the users table with id, email, name, created_at columns\n  **Acceptance**: migrations/001_create_users.sql exists. Running the migration creates the users table with all required columns.\n\nShuttle has responded: 'Failed. I created the migration file but the SQL syntax is incorrect — the migration runner reports: ERROR: syntax error at or near \"AUTOINCREMENT\" at line 3. PostgreSQL uses SERIAL or GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY, not AUTOINCREMENT.'\n\nWhat do you do next?"
  },
  "evaluators": [
    {
      "kind": "llm-judge",
      "expectedAnyOf": ["retry", "re-delegate", "delegate again", "error context", "attempt again", "try again"],
      "forbiddenContains": ["mark as blocked", "skip this task", "move on", "cannot complete"]
    }
  ]
}
